Usage: gem signin [options]

  Options:
        --host HOST                  Push to another gemcutter-compatible host
        --otp CODE                   Digit code for multifactor authentication


  Common Options:
    -h, --help                       Get help on this command
    -V, --[no-]verbose               Set the verbose level of output
    -q, --quiet                      Silence command progress meter
        --silent                     Silence RubyGems output
        --config-file FILE           Use this config file instead of default
        --backtrace                  Show stack backtrace on errors
        --debug                      Turn on Ruby debugging
        --norc                       Avoid loading any .gemrc file


  Summary:
    Sign in to any gemcutter-compatible host. It defaults to
    https://rubygems.org

  Description:
    The signin command executes host sign in for a push server (the default is
    https://rubygems.org). The host can be provided with the host flag or can be
    inferred from the provided gem. Host resolution matches the resolution
    strategy for the push command.
